summary: How can I help BTS succeed? (A Quick Guide)
body:
How can I help BTS succeed? (A Quick Guide)

BTS need YOUR help in order to make sure they stay on the western industry’s most prestigious charts (Billboard) and break down the cultural and societal borders that ignore the talent Asian artists work hard to polish and evolve.

It may sound tedious and like a lot of work but no worries! It’s not very hard to help out :)

What can you do?

  • Stream! How? Easily! Apple Music, Youtube, Spotify, etc. Each streaming platform does have free and paid versions. Paid versions are much stronger but if you cannot afford it, using free versions can help as well :)
  • Request BTS on Radio Stations! How? Search up your local radio station and see how you can possibly contact them (either text or phone, if you do not have a twitter account). Simply let them know your a fan of BTS and kindly request to hear their title track! (in this era, Fake Love)
  • Buy their Title Track/Album! If you have the money, it will really help BTS get on the charts if you can buy their title track and physical album separately.
  • Have a discussion with a friend/family member/co-worker etc about bts! This may be one of the simplest ways to help bts. Just start a civil and passionate conversation about bts. Many people may think that bts is only big because they’re a cute boy band, but for us armys, we know they’re something more than that. Let them know. More often than not, they’ll start to understand and look into bts themselves and then ultimately help them out!

Please know that you are not required to do all of these at once or any of them at all, but please know that our boys need us more than ever.

The general public is not going to help us. They’re still very skeptical about a boy band that are singing in a language that they don’t understand and it’s truly up to US to make sure that they know hat BTS is more than a boy group. They make beautiful compostions, captivating and relatable lyrics that more often than not comment on socio, political and economic disparities in our society, unorthodox and consistant storytelling patterns through various music videos, and a strong bond from not only their own group but their fans. They are more than a group. We need to show the general public that.

I hope this was useful, please dm me if you have any questions and I’ll try my best to answer them!

P.S. I’m still very new to tumblr so please bear with me while I figure out how to navigate through this platform

summary: BTS' "Fake Love" launches to No. 10, marking the first #Hot100 top 10 EVER for a K-pop group
title: BTS' "Fake Love" launches to No. 10, marking the first #Hot100 top 10 EVER for a K-pop group
body: Superstar Korean boy band BTS, whose “Fake Love” launches at No. 10, marking the first Hot 100 top 10 ever for a K-pop group, as parent album Love Yourself: Tear debuts as the group’s first No. 1 on the Billboard 200, where it’s also the first No. 1 for an album in the K-pop genre.

reblog.comment: Superstar Korean boy band BTS, whose “Fake Love” launches at No. 10, marking the first Hot 100 top 10 ever for a K-pop group, as parent album Love Yourself: Tear debuts as the group’s first No. 1 on the Billboard 200, where it’s also the first No. 1 for an album in the K-pop genre.

summary: Gangnam Style has the highest peak at HOT100 at #2, but it debut outside of top 10 and peaked at #2 after a week or so......
body:
Gangnam Style has the highest peak at HOT100 at #2, but it debut outside of top 10 and peaked at #2 after a week or so… Bangtan has the highest debut in HOT100 for all Korean acts at #10!!!

If we keep streaming we can even push it higher in the chart!! Even if you’re not in the US, if you stream using the official Spotify playlists where Fake Love is included it can help!!! This is such amazing achievement!! Thank you to everyone who streams and bought the single thank you for supporting bangtan so much!!! They’re gonna wake up to great news again!!!!
